description.narrative: UNICEF continued advocating for the strengthening of birth registration data and vital statistics to fulfill children’s rights and inform policy design, planning, and implementation, including the interoperability of health and justice systems. With UNICEF support, 9,550 children under five years old were digitally registered which was near government target (10,000). The emergency psycho-social support strategy served as good modelling and advocacy tools for an increased government commitment to prevent and address violence against children; the Ministry of Social Affairs established a specialized team of social workers to support families at community level, including addressing violence against children. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:03/02/2022
